						               													<description>THE BIG BANG THEORY Ultimate Genius Party Game features 4 different game challenges, each inspired from some of THE BIG BANG THEORY'S funniest moments.  Players are divided into 2-4 teams and roll a special die each turn to determine which game they will play. These games include Counterfactuals, Fun with Flags, Sketch Charades, and Celebrity.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In Counterfactuals, a member of the opposite team will draw a card that suppose a world that is different from our own in one key aspect, and asks a question about that world.  The competing teammates must choose from multiple-choice answers, and gain points if their answers match each other's, as well as if they match the game writers' answer.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The goal in Fun with Flags is for a player to guess flags from a deck of cards based on clues given by a teammate.  The twist is that there are 3 Oops Words that the Clue-Giver cannot say.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Sketch Charades is a simple drawing game, where one teammate will draw a card with a phrase, then has to draw it for another teammate to guess.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Finally, Celebrity is a charades game, in which one teammate is chosen to be the Actor and all the other teammates are the Guessers.  An opposing team chooses answers for each of 5 categories for the Actor to act out.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
